snippet.textDisplay:
What witnesses said Thelma was dropped off at her restaurant at all? And as for where she could have been, out driving with someone else and eating dinner at unknown places, well one thing stands out to me. Why could it not have been her chauffeur? I mean, if the guy breaks too hard or has a little fender bender or something on the way back to dropping her off after her dinner of peas and carrots, that impact could break her nose or crack a couple of ribs and knock her right out. The dude could panic and, not knowing that she has a key to the building in her purse and not wanting to check, drops her off in her own car at West's garage. He doesn't want to be fired for breaking a starlet's nose and knocking her out with his poor driving or whatever, after all. And, because he doesn't want her to get hypothermia (or to kill her off for real to save his career and to avoid arrest if she sic's the cops on him once coming to), he turns on the car and closes the garage door behind him on his way out.

Idk, it made some sense to me.
